snippet.textDisplay:
Can people get their facts right.
1st Klopp wanted to rest his team as they have a league game and champions starting soon, no point trying to win a cup that is unbenificial and forces teams to play, just because.

2nd Klopp didn't want to manage the team because the U23 team had their own coach and wanted their coach to continue coaching them.

3rd. It's the U23 team, not the U19... hints why their YOUNGEST was 22... 😂

4th FA hates Klopp because Klopp is doing what the other big teams have been doing for years in the FA Cup. It's just this year the FA officials decided they were going to be strict about big teams not taking it seriously but then don't respect big teams for trying to have a break whilst competing in more valuable cups / Leagues.

Also they won't allow any dates to be rearranged as Klopp tried to do this but the FA refused to reschedule any games for Liverpool. Hints why Klopp isn't bothered about it. If he wins it, it's just a middle finger at the officials for trying to boast their "power".

The FA cup is only good for lower end clubs as it gives them a chance to earn so extra pocket money, nothing benificial for higher end teams.
